<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="468" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10552: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-08T13:00:00+08:00">October 8, 1929—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:57 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>867. Following from American Consul General at Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“At 10 a.m. Thursday steamship <hi rend="italic">Iling</hi> of
                                    Yangtze Rapids Steamship Company was fired on by Chinese troops
                                    at mileage 219 above Hankow. Ship struck 6 times, but no
                                    casualties. I have lodged protest with Commissioner of Foreign
                                    Affairs.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>